  "text": "Kiesmüller and van der Laan (2001) and Kelle and Silver (1989) considered the situation where return product quantity is probability correlated with product demand. Toktay et al. (2000) predicted probability densities for the return probability and the return delay based on real-time sales and return data by applying Bayesian statistics and survival analysis. [CITATION_1] suggested that it is reasonable to select historical information about sales and returns in terms of products' characteristics when predicting return quantity.",
